title: Storm Center Update - Sunday PM
text:
Storm Center Update - Sunday PM October 11, 2015, 3:32 PM by Grant Smith 
Sunday afternoon in KELOLAND was filled with plenty of sunshine, temperatures that felt more like July, and strong winds that remind us we live in great open plains of the Midwest. Afternoon temperatures reached the 80s and 90s once again today and as of 3:30PM, reported wind gusts have been as high 65 mph. 
The wind advisories and high wind warnings will continue through the evening for a good portion of KELOLAND. These are for the continued expected wind gusts up to 60 mph this evening and part of the overnight. Overnight lows in the 40s and 50s. 
Monday evening the winds will calm down but you can still expect breezy winds through the work day. Afternoon temperatures will be a little cooler tomorrow, reaching the 60s. 
The rest of the week will have afternoon temps a little bit more seasonal with highs in the 60s and 70s.
